                    <h2 class="section-heading">Location</h2>
                    <hr class="light">
                    <p class="text-faded">The Lodge can be approached from Kampala
Through Mbarara Town approximately 5-6 hour drive (363km) on a tarmac highway
 Or through Fort Portal a 5-7 hour drive(376km) on a tarmac highway</p>
<br/>

<p class="text-faded"><strong>Mbarara Route</strong><br/>
The Lodge is off the main Mbarara-Kasese tarmac road 100km North of Mbarara. About 80km down this route, the drive is through beautiful landscape dominated by Kyamuhunga Tea estates which borders an expanse of Maramagambo thick tropical forest.
About 3kms from Ndekye town, you turn off to the left of the tarmac highway on to the gravel road. The Lodge is located about 2kms from the tarmac highway.</p>
<br/>

<p class="text-faded"><strong>Fort Portal Route</strong><br/>
From Fort Portal, drive about 76kms to Kasese Town then continue on the Kasese-Mbarara Highway which for most of the way passes through Queen Elizabeth National Park. Drive across the Katungwa Bridge over Kazinga Channel (about 38kms from Kasese).
About 24kms from the bridge, turn off to the right of the tarmac highway on to the gravel road. The lodge is about 2km from the tarmac highway.</p>
<br/>
